Comment_contributor: no similarity between the word for ‘five’: ‘palpalima’, and the word for ‘hand’: ‘kunga’
Comment_glosser: Possibly derived historically via sequential number word formation with reduplication of preceding 4, and 5 meaning ‘hand’ (from POc *minV- ‘hand’) (?)
The form <na> would seem to mean ‘and’, but if it is also used in multiplication (as in 20 and 50), then it is perhaps a more general ligature
